Lesson Components

Text and Markdown
Use standard Markdown syntax:
# Heading 1
## Heading 2

**Bold text**
*Italic text*

- Bullet list
1. Numbered list

[Link text](url)


Images
Place images in an assets/ folder within your lesson directory:
![Image description](assets/dna-structure.png)


Videos
Embed videos using HTML:
```{=html}
&lt;video width="100%" controls&gt;
  &lt;source src="assets/video.mp4" type="video/mp4"&gt;
&lt;/video&gt;

Or embed from external sources:

```markdown
```{=html}
&lt;iframe width="560" height="315" 
  src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/VIDEO_ID" 
  frameborder="0" allowfullscreen&gt;
&lt;/iframe&gt;

### Callouts and Alerts

Use Quarto's built-in callout blocks:

```markdown
:::{.callout-note}
This is an important note for students.
:::

:::{.callout-tip}
Here's a helpful tip!
:::

:::{.callout-warning}
Pay attention to this warning.
:::


Interactive Quizzes
Create quiz pages with HTML forms:
&lt;form id="quiz"&gt;
  &lt;div class="question"&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;1. What is DNA?&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;label&gt;&lt;input type="radio" name="q1" value="a"&gt; Answer A&lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;label&gt;&lt;input type="radio" name="q1" value="b"&gt; Answer B&lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;label&gt;&lt;input type="radio" name="q1" value="c"&gt; Answer C&lt;/label&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;button type="submit"&gt;Submit Quiz&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;

&lt;script&gt;
document.getElementById('quiz').addEventListener('submit', function(e) {
  e.preventDefault();
  // Quiz logic here
  alert('Quiz submitted!');
});
&lt;/script&gt;


Code Blocks
Display code with syntax highlighting:
```python
def analyze_dna(sequence):
    return sequence.upper()
```
